# Review/Retrospective Pattern - Personal Automation Framework
# Adapted from BMM retrospective workflow on 2025-12-22

This pattern shows how to conduct personal reviews and retrospectives - adapted from BMAD's epic retrospective.

## Concept: From Epic Retrospective to Personal Review

**Software Development (BMM):**
- Reviews completed epic (set of stories)
- Team discussion of what went well/poorly
- Extract lessons learned
- Plan improvements for next epic

**Personal Life (Adapted):**
- Reviews completed period (week/month/quarter)
- Self-reflection on what worked/didn't
- Extract lessons and insights
- Plan adjustments for next period

## Review Types

### 1. Weekly Review
**Duration:** 15-30 minutes
**Frequency:** End of week (Sunday evening)
**Scope:** Past 7 days

**Questions:**
- What did I accomplish this week?
- What didn't get done? Why?
- What worked well?
- What struggled?
- What do I want to change next week?

### 2. Monthly Review
**Duration:** 45-60 minutes
**Frequency:** Last day of month
**Scope:** Past month

**Questions:**
- What goals did I complete?
- What goals are in progress?
- What goals stalled? Why?
- What surprised me this month?
- What patterns emerged?
- What do I want to focus on next month?

### 3. Quarterly Review
**Duration:** 2-3 hours
**Frequency:** End of quarter
**Scope:** Past 3 months

**Questions:**
- What were my biggest wins?
- What were my biggest learnings?
- What didn't work? What will I stop doing?
- What do I want to start doing?
- How am I tracking toward annual goals?

### 4. Annual Review
**Duration:** Half day to full day
**Frequency:** End of year
**Scope:** Full year

**Questions:**
- What am I most proud of this year?
- What would I do differently?
- What did I learn about myself?
- What relationships did I strengthen?
- What goals did I achieve?
- What do I want next year to be about?

